Nils Aguilar:

"Origin:  from Náhuatl mil-li-pan ‘what shall be sown onto the field’.

Agricultural system used throughout Mesoamerica, based on the ancient methods of the Mayas and other Mesoamerican peoples.

A milpa field is highly diverse : different crops are being mixed in with each other, including various varieties of maize, beans and squash (commonly referred to as the ‘three sisters’) as well as avocados, melons, tomatoes, amaranth, etc.

The use of this traditional, sacred crop system conserves local knowledge, enables farmers to control their genetic resources and provides for local subsistence."
(http://www.milpafilms.org/milpa.php/?page_id=12)


